listing.notes:
I would like to trade this copy of Scythe to someone who will appreciate it more. It has seen light play (twenty or so times), all components are in excellent condition. The cover of the box has a slightly bent top left corner (as seen on picture) which I think is due to the original transport.

This was the most expensive Kickstarter tier, and it includes:
- numbered box;
- the hardcover art book;
- large map;
- metal coins (plus the original ones);
- deluxe realistic resources (no wooden ones);
- four Stonemeier-branded plastic containers for the resources;
- all other Kickstarter exclusives/promos.

It also includes an aftermarket Feldherr foam tray insert (https://www.feldherr.net/foam-tray-value-set-for-the-scythe-board-game-box/a-57018). It raises the box cover about a cm or so; also, when it's inside the box, there is no place for the original plastic resource and mech containers, but I do keep them and will happily send them along.

Ideally, this would be a local pickup, and I would LOVE to trade it down to a base copy of Scythe (with the metal coins, if possible) plus payment. 

If you are abroad, please note that this box is both large and HEAVY. Local trades preferred. I can get pretty good shipping quotes for this game with DPD to most EU countries.
